  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best way to clean house windows?",
  "response": "Cleaning house windows effectively involves a few straightforward steps and the right supplies. Here\u2019s a tried-and-true method:\n\n### Materials Needed:\n- Bucket\n- Squeegee\n- Microfiber cloth or lint-free cloth\n- Soft sponge or window scrubber\n- Mild dish soap or a window cleaning solution\n- Vinegar (optional, for extra shine)\n- Water\n- Ladder (if needed for higher windows)\n- Rubber gloves (optional for protection)\n\n### Steps:\n\n1. **Prepare the Cleaning Solution:**\n   - Mix a few drops of mild dish soap into a bucket of warm water. Alternatively, you can use a mix of equal parts water and vinegar for added shine.\n\n2. **Remove Dust and Debris:**\n   - Before washing, remove any dust or loose debris using a dry microfiber cloth or a soft brush. This prevents scratching the glass during cleaning.\n\n3. **Wash the Windows:**\n   - Dip a soft sponge or window scrubber into the cleaning solution. Gently scrub the window in a circular motion, paying extra attention to any spots or stains.\n\n4. **Squeegee the Window:**\n   - Starting at the top corner of the window, pull the squeegee down in a straight line. Wipe the blade with a clean cloth after each stroke to prevent streaks.\n   - Overlap each stroke slightly to avoid leaving lines.\n\n5. **Dry and Polish:**\n   - Use a microfiber cloth or a lint-free cloth to wipe any remaining water from the edges and corners of the window.\n   - For extra shine, buff the glass with a dry cloth.\n\n6. **Clean Window Frames and Sills:**\n   - Don\u2019t forget to wipe down the window frames and sills with a damp cloth, and dry them thoroughly to prevent damage.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- **Choose the Right Time:** Clean windows on a cloudy day or when the windows are in the shade to prevent the cleaning solution from drying too quickly and leaving streaks.\n- **Screen Care:** If your windows have screens, remove them and rinse with water. Let them dry before reinstalling.\n- **Safety First:** Use a sturdy ladder for higher windows, and consider using an extension pole if possible. Always prioritize safety.\n\nBy following these steps, you can achieve sparkling clean windows that enhance the look of your home both inside and out.",
